05:12.340 --> 05:15.980
Each element absorbs a different set of wavelengths.

05:15.980 --> 05:20.100
We can see these absorption patterns as lines when we look through an instrument called

05:20.100 --> 05:21.700
a spectroscope.

05:21.700 --> 05:25.820
This one shows the spectral lines of three elements that were very familiar to early

05:25.820 --> 05:30.940
19th century scientists, hydrogen, lithium and oxygen.

05:30.940 --> 05:36.940
But when the French astronomer Pierre Janssen pointed a spectroscope at the Sun in 1868,

05:36.940 --> 05:40.740
he found a set of spectral lines no one had ever seen before.

05:40.740 --> 05:43.340
It was a completely unknown element.

05:43.340 --> 05:47.620
He called it helium, after the Greek word helios, the Sun.

05:47.620 --> 05:53.660
The new element also showed up in stars, along with another abundant element, hydrogen.

05:53.660 --> 05:57.780
Inside this tightly bound universe, which they called the galaxy, astronomers could

05:57.780 --> 06:01.420
see strange swirling clouds through their telescopes.

06:01.420 --> 06:06.380
Some astronomers thought these could be other galaxies, just like our own.

06:06.380 --> 06:12.900
In 1917, a supernova was seen to explode inside a cloud called Andromeda.

06:12.900 --> 06:17.460
Supernovas are usually very bright, but this one was quite faint.

06:17.460 --> 06:22.780
Using the brightness and distance calculation, cosmologists work out just how far away Andromeda

06:22.780 --> 06:25.780
was, two million light years.

06:25.780 --> 06:31.780
That put it well outside our own galaxy, and triangulation showed just how big it was,

06:31.780 --> 06:34.140
about the size of our own galaxy.

06:34.140 --> 06:39.460
The universe, it turned out, extended well beyond our own cluster of stars, and millions

06:39.460 --> 06:42.740
of years back in time.

06:42.740 --> 06:47.700
American astronomer Edwin Hubble soon discovered that other galaxies were even further away.

06:47.700 --> 06:52.660
He also confirmed an observation that they were all moving away from us at incredible

06:52.660 --> 06:53.660
speed.

06:53.660 --> 06:56.260
